range_n_clusters = [2, 3, 4, 5, 6]
for n_clusters in range_n_clusters:   
    clusterer = KMeans(n_clusters=n_clusters, random_state=10)
    cluster_labels = clusterer.fit_predict(X_wine)
    silhouette_avg = silhouette_score(X_wine, cluster_labels)
    print("For n_clusters =", n_clusters,
          "The average silhouette_score is :", silhouette_avg)

    # Compute the silhouette scores for each sample
    sample_silhouette_values = silhouette_samples(X_wine, cluster_labels)

# fine tuning
mat2 = X_wine.to_numpy()

scaler = StandardScaler()

algorithm = (KMeans(n_clusters = 2 ,init='k-means++', n_init = 30 ,max_iter=300, 
                        tol=0.0005,  random_state= 12  , algorithm='elkan') )

labels1 = algorithm.labels_

# list to save the clusters and cost
clusters = []
inertia_vals = []

# this whole process should take a while
for k in range(2, 15, 2):
    # train clustering with the specified K
    model = KMeans(n_clusters=k, random_state=12, n_jobs=10)
    model.fit(X_cancer)
    
    # append model to cluster list
    clusters.append(model)
    inertia_vals.append(model.inertia_)

i) wine and cancer data¶

In [27]:
from collections import defaultdict

clusters = np.arange(1,10)
covTypeList = ['full', 'tied', 'diag', 'spherical']

for X in [X_cancer, X_wine]:
    aicDict = defaultdict(list)
    bicDict = defaultdict(list)
    for covType in covTypeList:
        for n in clusters:
            gm = GaussianMixture(n_components=n, covariance_type=covType, max_iter=500, n_init=5, reg_covar=1e-2)
            gm.fit(X)
            aic = gm.aic(X)
            bic = gm.bic(X)
            aicDict[covType].append(aic)
            bicDict[covType].append(bic)

    plt.figure(figsize=(12,4))


    plt.subplot(1,2,1)
    for key, value in aicDict.items():
        plt.plot(clusters, value, label=key)
    plt.ylabel('AIC score')
    plt.xlabel("number of clusters")
    plt.yscale('log')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('AIC')

    plt.subplot(1,2,2)
    for key, value in bicDict.items():
        plt.plot(clusters, value, label=key)
    plt.ylabel('BIC score')
    plt.xlabel("number of clusters")
    plt.yscale('log')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('BIC')

    plt.tight_layout()

# K-means
algs = {'PCA': PCA(n_components=2,random_state=12),
        'ICA': FastICA(n_components=2, random_state=12),
        'Randomized Projections': GaussianRandomProjection(n_components=2, random_state=12),
        'RandomForest': RandomForestClassifier(random_state=123)}

for k in algs.keys():
    if k == 'RandomForest':
        model = algs[k]
        lr = model.fit(XX_wine, y_wine)
        
        ascending_order = np.argsort(lr.feature_importances_)
        feature_index = ascending_order[::-1][:3]
        Xproj = XX_wine[:,feature_index]
        
    else:
        model = algs[k]
        Xproj = model.fit_transform(X_wine)
        
    km = KMeans(n_clusters=2, random_state=0)
    km.fit(Xproj)
    print(k,'model')
    print('Accuracy',accuracy_score(y_wine, km.labels_))
    cm = confusion_matrix(y_wine, km.labels_)
    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, cmap="YlGnBu")
    plt.ylabel('actual')
    plt.xlabel('prediction')
    plt.title(k)
    plt.show()
